  "text": "UNMs and TCP were prepared as follows: the anthers at the uninucleate and tricellular stages were crashed gently in 0.4 M mannitol at 4°C; the resulting slurry was filtered through 150 μm and subsequent 100 μm nylon mesh to remove anther debris, through 60 μm nylon mesh to remove cell debris, and finally through 30 μm nylon mesh to collect pollen. Bicellular pollen (BCP) was collected as described [CITATION_1] with several modifications. Briefly, the anthers containing BCP were collected and gently ground in 0.4 M mannitol at 4°C. After filtering subsequently through 150 μm and 60 μm nylon mesh, the pollen was harvested by centrifugation at 500 g for 5 min at 4°C, and then purified by 25%/30%/45%/80% Percoll (Pharmacia) step gradient under 500 g centrifugation for 5 min at 4°C. Resulting BCP cells were collected from the 30%/45% fraction, pelleted by centrifugation at 500 g for 5 min at 4°C, and washed with 0.4 M mannitol. Mature pollen grains (MPGs) were collected at anthesis stage [CITATION_2] . Germinated pollen grains (GPGs) were obtained as described [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . The purity of the isolated pollen was determined by examination on light microscopy (Carl Zeiss) after 4',6-diaminophenylindole (DAPI) (Molecular Probes) staining, and viability of mature pollen was assessed by fluorescein 3',6'-diacetate (FDA) staining [CITATION_5] . Germination ratio of mature pollen grains was evaluated on microscopy after culture in germination medium in vitro (Carl Zeiss).",
